cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on detecting fraud in online social networks, specifically Facebook, using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses fraud detection algorithms and the shortcomings of graph-based detection tools, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper analyzes content generated by social network accounts, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of features extracted from timeline posts, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
